# Implement provider_cohere.ml (Command R+ /v2/chat, tool-use format)

## Requirements

- Create `src/provider_cohere.ml` implementing `complete` and `complete_stream` against `POST https://api.cohere.ai/v2/chat` with `Authorization: Bearer {api_key}`. The message structure differs from OpenAI: messages use `role = "user" | "assistant"` (no `"system"` role in message list); system prompt is passed as a top-level `system` string field.
- Parse the non-streaming response: `message.content[0].text` for text → `Provider.Text`. Tool calls appear as `message.tool_calls[].{id, type:"tool", function.{name, arguments}}` — same field names as OpenAI, so mapping is straightforward. Map to `Provider.ToolCalls`.
- For streaming, Cohere SSE returns events with `event_type` field: `event_type = "content-delta"` carries `delta.message.content.text`; `event_type = "tool-call-start"` and `"tool-call-delta"` carry partial tool JSON. Accumulate and emit `Provider.stream_event` values. Wire dispatch via `Cohere` kind from T001.

## Implementation Notes

- `detect_kind` heuristic: model name starting with `"command"` (e.g., `"command-r-plus"`) → `Cohere`; or `kind = "cohere"` config field (T008).
- Base URL default: `https://api.cohere.ai`. Endpoint: `base_url ^ "/v2/chat"`. Note the plan references `/v2/chat` (not `/v1/chat`).
- Tool definitions in requests use `tools[].{name, description, parameter_definitions}` in Cohere v1 format, or `tools[].{type:"function", function.{name,description,parameters}}` in v2 — use the v2 format to align with existing `tools` JSON passed from `agent.ml`.
- Add `provider_cohere` to `clawq_runtime_core` in `src/dune`. No new dependencies.

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- A user message list is serialized to Cohere v2 format with `system` at top level and `messages` containing only `role=user|assistant` entries.
- A response body `{message:{content:[{type:"text",text:"Hello"}]}}` is parsed to `Text {content="Hello"; ...}`.
- `detect_kind` returns `Cohere` for model name `"command-r-plus"`.
- `make test` passes.
